name: Jaclyn Peters Design
bio: manitoba based interior design studio creating casual, collected, luxury homes for modern living.

social_posts.post_text: Merry Christmas to you from my little fam (and the best addition we made this year Miss Leni🐶!) Even though I’ve taken a little social media hiatus, I promise we’re still here doing our thing and designing beautiful homes. I can’t wait to share what @amywaltersdesign and I have been working on for the last couple of years! Here’s to all the good things to come in 2023!

my favorite part of my job is getting to design homes in a myriad of styles while staying true to our unique, layered, and clean modern aesthetic. Swipe to see what we started with before gutting and remodeling this mid-century home in Tuxedo!
sharing another before and after of our Tuxedo Mid-Century project, and officially declaring maroon a neutral color.

what I wouldn’t give to have a mud room like this! In our Tuxedo Mid-Century project we turned a dysfunctional room into this beautiful workhorse of a space. We removed the secondary fireplace, enlarged the living room, replaced the small windows with one large window, and added a new entry to the garage!
always up for a mid-century reno ✨
our take on mid century: a classic white kitchen but make her extra special with statement stone, reeded walnut millwork and brass half moon island legs 🌙
Original staircase ➕ a few coats of pitch-black paint 🖤

Don’t want to jinx it but I think it’s finally time to put the winter boots away ☀️ 
#jpdtuxedomidcentury
mixing all the neutrals at our Tuxedo mid-century project.

a moody powder bath is always a good idea. 

Photo by @arianatennyson

Thank you @houseandhomemag for including me in your inaugural top 100 designers in Canada for 2023! I am incredibly honored, and can’t wait to pick up the December issue (available November 17th) to see the amazing talent I am alongside. Also a huge thank you to my small but mighty team of two. I couldn’t do what I do without you! 🤍
